verbose_text: Notably, knockdown of GNAI3 by lentiviral vectors expressing short-hairpin RNAs against GNAI3 significantly inhibited the proliferation, cell cycle progression and migration of SCAPs, as well as odonto / osteogenic differentiation of SCAPs in vitro, suggesting that GNAI3 may play an essential role in tooth root development.
